tags.name: Match
tags.description:
Match data is meant to store historical match information - including players, and related metadata.

Matches are searchable on the Support Portal, and there are endpoints to query a player's matches or all matches in the system.

Each match can also contain many Match Segments - which are sub-components of the overall match.  They contain the same fields as the match.  Common usage of Match Segments would be laps of a race to record player positions, minute intervals to record the state of the game partway through, rounds of play, or minigames within a larger match.

tags.name: Player Experience
tags.description: Player Experience (PEX) is a system for Clients/Hosts to post metrics to for top-level analysis.
